						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2a01009cd70bcefe8a5ccf745ee96ba8?s=42&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2a01009cd70bcefe8a5ccf745ee96ba8?s=84&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' loading='lazy'/>						<b class="fn"><a href='http://www.wdfpublishing.com' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Dave Frolick</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://alumni.blog.ryerson.ca/2018/01/05/attention-baby-boomers-are-you-ready-to-reinvent-yourself/#comment-43">
							<time datetime="2018-01-11T11:24:08-05:00">
								January 11, 2018 at 11:24 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I just read John Bell&#8217;s blog about following his passion and writing a novel when he retired. A few years ago, in my retirement, I decided to write a murder mystery novel. Actually, I have written two murder mystery novels, The Cabin: A murder Mystery and Music City Murders. I write under the name W.D. Frolick. Both books are self-published under my own publishing name, WDF Publishing  They are available on all Amazon sites and most e-book sites as well. Like John, I&#8217;m a Business Administration graduate (class of &#8217;64).</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
